<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="155" pageId="3" pageNumber="154" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1801,2009]" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,509,1945,1970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[521,844,1945,1970]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Ptychoglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="3" pageNumber="154" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevifrontalis">
<emphasis box="[521,844,1945,1970]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Ptychoglossus brevifrontalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in, 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1189,1945,1970]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="3" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
, occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[1360,1431,1945,1970]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,264,1984,2009]" name="Colombia" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[279,374,1984,2009]" name="Ecuador" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[439,490,1985,2008]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[510,582,1984,2009]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1331,1353]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,413,1310]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,403,1315]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of examined material of Alopoglossus buckleyi and Ptychoglossus brevifrontalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581977/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[640,753,1984,2009]" name="Colombia" pageId="3" pageNumber="154">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, it also occurs in forested areas adjacent to the Llanos.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<bibRefCitation author="Hoogmoed" box="[151,360,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" refString="Hoogmoed, M. S. (1973) Notes on the herpetofauna of Surinam. IV. The lizards and amphisbaenians of Surinam. Biogeographica, 4, 1 - 419." type="journal article" year="1973">Hoogmoed (1973)</bibRefCitation>
also reported it from Suriname, 
<bibRefCitation box="[743,960,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" refString="Rivas, G. A., Molina, C. R., Ugueto, G. N., Barros, T. R., Barrio-Amoros, C. L. &amp; Kok, P. J. R. (2012) Reptiles of Venezuela: an updated and commented checklist. Zootaxa, 3211, 1 - 64." type="journal article">
Rivas 
<emphasis box="[816,868,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">et al</emphasis>
. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
from Venezuela, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Harris" box="[1217,1371,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" refString="Harris, D. M. (1994) Review of the teiid lizard genus Ptychoglossus. Herpetological Monographs, 8, 226 - 275. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1467082" type="journal article" year="1994">Harris (1994)</bibRefCitation>
from Bolivia. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1503410444" country="Brazil" location="Amapa" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Amapa">
In 
<collectingCountry box="[284,355,188,213]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is known from the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[726,810,188,212]" country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Amapá</collectingRegion>
, Pará, Amazonas, 
<collectingRegion box="[1027,1084,188,212]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Acre</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1150,1263,188,213]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Ptychoglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevifrontalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Ptychoglossus brevifrontalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits primary terra firme forest (Gardner 
<emphasis box="[1103,1161,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">et al.</emphasis>
2006; Ávila-Pires 
<emphasis box="[1378,1436,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">et al.</emphasis>
2010; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro-Junior" box="[221,511,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" refString="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A.; R. V. Rossi; C. L. Miranda &amp; T. C. S. Avila-Pires. (2011) Influence of pitfall trap size and design on herpetofauna and small mammal studies in a Neotropical forest. Zoologia, 28, 80 - 91. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1984 - 46702011000100012" type="journal article" year="2011">
Ribeiro-Júnior 
<emphasis box="[390,446,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
), where it is found on the ground, among leaf litter (usually in areas with dense and deep leaf litter—Dixon &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Soini" box="[445,569,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" refString="Dixon, J. R. &amp; Soini, P. (1975) The reptiles of the upper Amazon Basin, Iquitos region, Peru. Part 1. Lizards and Amphisbaenians. Milwaukee Public Museum, Contributions in Biology and Geology, 4, 1 - 58." type="journal article" year="1975">Soini 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Soini" box="[580,640,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" refString="Dixon, J. R. &amp; Soini, P. (1986) The reptiles of the upper Amazon Basin, Iquitos region, Peru. Milwaukee Public Museum, Milwaukee, 154 pp." type="book" year="1986">1986</bibRefCitation>
), under rocks and rotten tree trunks (
<bibRefCitation author="Duellman" box="[1049,1226,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" refString="Duellman, W. E. (1978) The biology of an Equatorial herpetofauna in Amazonian Ecuador. Miscellaneous Publications, Museum of Natural History of University of Kansas, 65, 1 - 352." type="journal article" year="1978">Duellman 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Avila-Pires" box="[1238,1431,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" refString="Avila-Pires, T. C. S. (1995) Lizards of Brazilian Amazonia (Reptilia: Squamata). Zoologische Ferhandelingen, 299, 1 - 706." type="journal article" year="1995">Ávila-Pires 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vitt" box="[151,324,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" refString="Vitt, L. J., Magnusson, W. E., Avila-Pires, T. C. S. &amp; Lima, A. P. (2008) Guia de Lagartos da Reserva Adolpho Ducke, Amazonia Central = Guide to the Lizards of Reserva Adolpho Ducke, Central Amazonia. Attema Design Editorial, Manaus, 176 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / issn. 2316 - 9079. v 6 i 1 p 73 - 76" type="book" year="2008">
Vitt 
<emphasis box="[200,256,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
